                    <div class="question">Do we need to be tech-savvy to be considered?</div>
                    <div class="switchicon">
                        <img src="https://assets-global.website-files.com/611678a38604517d3bd8ef0c/611e7a63bb7311d2d8ea2b32_close.svg" loading="lazy" alt="" class="closeicon"/>
                        <img src="https://assets-global.website-files.com/611678a38604517d3bd8ef0c/611e7a46aac87d1d13e1c3a2_open.svg" loading="lazy" alt="" class="openicon"/>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="answer">
                    <p class="faqparagraph">
                        No, both small and big, tech-savvy or new-to-digital organizations can use WhatsApp successfully. You must have a strong business case/theory of change for using digital messaging such as WhatsApp.
                        <br/>
                        <br/>
